    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      The initialize method for the Add Appointment view. This method is called when the view is launched and contains methods for populating the combo boxes for the form.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable

    • populateComboBoxes

      public void populateComboBoxes() throws SQLException
      This method populates the combo boxes for the form. Each combo box uses a method to get an ObservableList for each respective combo box.
      Throws:
      SQLException

    • inputCheck

      public boolean inputCheck()
      Returns:
      - This method checks if each field in the form is filled, and returns true or false. If any one of the fields is empty when user tries to add an appointment, an alert window launches.

    • goodAppointmentTime

      public boolean goodAppointmentTime() throws SQLException
      Returns:
      - This method checks if the user's Start and End Times are appropriate and returns true or false. It checks the following time possibilities: - End time is before Start time - Start and End Time is the same - Compares against open office hours (Eastern Time) - Overlapping appointments of the same customer.
      Throws:
      SQLException

    • insertAppointment

      public void insertAppointment() throws SQLException
      This method gets the values from each field of the form and sends it to the AppointmentDAO to an INSERT statement to the database. First, two methods (inputCheck and goodAppointmentTime) check if inputs are filled and if the Start and End Times are appropriate.
      Throws:
      SQLException

    • resetFields

      public void resetFields()
      This method clears all the fields. Setting the form empty gives the option to the user to quickly start over the entry.

    • toSchedulerDashboard

      public void toSchedulerDashboard(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      This method brings the user back to the main scheduling dashboard.
      Throws:
      IOException
